        <scopecontent>
          <p>Personal/Research (0.7 linear ft.; 1971-1993) documents Marzolf's personal research and interests. Three subseries, Awards, Research, and Women In Communication, Inc. (WICI) are arranged alphabetically by topic. Her research on the Michigan Ethnic Press includes surveys conducted for her book and provides a wealth of information about the ethnic press and its development throughout the state. Divided by ethnic group, these surveys provide the dates and places of publication for newspapers throughout the state. Numerous conference papers and unpublished works are also included in this series. Records and reports from the student chapter of Women in Communication, Inc., for which Marzolf served as an advisor, document not only her years as advisor but also the activities of the organization.</p>
        </scopecontent>
