          <unittitle>Teaching <unitdate type="inclusive" normal="1961/1994">1961-1994</unitdate></unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>Teaching (1.00 linear ft.; 1961-1995) consists of Marzolf's course materials from classes taught in journalism, communication and in both the American Culture and the Scandinavian Studies Programs. Materials from American Culture, Communications, and Journalism are arranged by course number. Her teaching syllabi from thirty plus years in journalism and communication comprise the bulk of this series; however, some courses have complete sets of notes and teaching materials. One of the first courses she taught at the University of Michigan, probably as a teaching assistant, is documented as well as the course in Basic Newswriting, which she supervised. Information Gathering for Mass Media (Com. 250/Jrn. 500), a course funded by a grant, is also completely documented.</p>
        </scopecontent>
